2011/3/9  <nix@myproxylists.com>:
> Can't get it working in a script. Tried both vt100/xterm terminals but na=
da.
> My purpose is this:
>
> while [ : ] ; do
>
> ...
>
> A user press the space button and he will see the script progress ....
>
> done

Then it's unrelated to bindkey ;-)

Try this:

while [ : ]; do
    read -ks a
    [[ $a =3D ' ' ]] && foo
done

Have a look at =E2=80=9Cman zshbuiltins=E2=80=9D for more about the =E2=80=
=9Cread=E2=80=9D builtin.

